  "_comment": "3-stage pipelined 3-bit ripple-carry adder. Each stage processes one bit of the sum and propagates the carry forward through a multi-channel PIPE_REG. Inputs A=(a2,a1,a0) and B=(b2,b1,b0) step through 6 operand pairs; with the 2-cycle pipeline latency, the first valid sum appears on cycle 3 and a new sum lands every cycle after that (II=1). Watch the OUTPUTs change across cycles: 0+0, 1+1, 3+2, 7+1 (overflow → COUT=1), 5+3, 4+4. Compared to a single combinational adder (which would be 3× the propagation delay), pipelining trades latency for throughput. Stages are perfectly balanced (1 FULL_ADDER per stage = 150 ps) — Balance 100%, f_max = 1/150ps.",
